# skill: security-scan
# purpose: Run automated security scans (Security Persona - Phase 3)
# triggers: Before shipping

## Invocation
```
security-scan <task-id> [--target <code-directory>] [--all-scans]
```

## Output
Creates: `memory/tasks/<task-id>/security-scan-results.md`

## Implementation Flow

### 1. Run All Scans
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# security-scan.skill implementation

TASK_ID="$1"
TARGET="${2:-.}"

echo "========================================="
echo "Running Security Scans for $TASK_ID"
echo "========================================="

mkdir -p "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans"

# 1. Secret Detection
echo "[1/6] Scanning for secrets..."
if command -v gitleaks &> /dev/null; then
    gitleaks detect --source "$TARGET" \
        --report-path "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/gitleaks.json" \
        --report-format json \
        2>/dev/null
else
    echo "  gitleaks not found, skipping..."
fi

# 2. SAST (Static Analysis)
echo "[2/6] Running SAST..."
if command -v semgrep &> /dev/null; then
    semgrep scan "$TARGET" --config auto \
        --output "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/semgrep.json" \
        --json 2>/dev/null
else
    echo "  semgrep not found, skipping..."
fi

# 3. Dependency Scanning - Python
echo "[3/6] Checking Python dependencies..."
if [ -f "$TARGET/requirements.txt" ] && command -v pip-audit &> /dev/null; then
    pip-audit -r "$TARGET/requirements.txt" \
        --format json \
        > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/pip-audit.json" 2>/dev/null
fi

# 4. Dependency Scanning - Node.js
echo "[4/6] Checking Node.js dependencies..."
if [ -f "$TARGET/package.json" ] && command -v npm &> /dev/null; then
    npm audit --json \
        > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/npm-audit.json" 2>/dev/null
fi

# 5. Infrastructure Scanning
echo "[5/6] Checking infrastructure files..."
if command -v checkov &> /dev/null; then
    checkov -d "$TARGET" \
        --report-format json \
        --output-file-path "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/checkov.json" 2>/dev/null
fi

# 6. Container Scanning
echo "[6/6] Checking Dockerfiles..."
if command -v hadolint &> /dev/null; then
    find "$TARGET" -name "Dockerfile*" -exec hadolint {} \; \
        > "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/hadolint.txt" 2>/dev/null
fi

echo "========================================="
echo "Scans complete. Results in:"
echo "  memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/scans/"
echo "========================================="
```

### 2. Generate Scan Report
```bash
generate_scan_report() {
    local task_id="$1"

    cat > "memory/tasks/$task_id/security-scan-results.md" << EOF
# Security Scan Results: $task_id

## Scan Summary
**Task:** $task_id
**Scanned:** \$(date +%Y-%m-%d)
**Target:** $TARGET

## Results Overview

| Scan | Tool | Issues | Status |
|------|------|--------|---|
| Secrets | gitleaks | <n> | ✓/✗ |
| SAST | semgrep | <n> | ✓/✗ |
| Python deps | pip-audit | <n> | ✓/✗ |
| Node deps | npm audit | <n> | ✓/✗ |
| Infra | checkov | <n> | ✓/✗ |
| Docker | hadolint | <n> | ✓/✗ |

## Critical Findings
\`\`\`
<from gitleaks results>
\`\`\`

## High Findings
\`\`\`
<from semgrep/npm-audit results>
\`\`\`

## Medium Findings
\`\`\`
<from all scans>
\`\`\`

## Detailed Results
See individual scan results in \`memory/tasks/$task_id/scans/\`

## Recommendations
1. Address all critical findings before merge
2. Review and remediate high-priority findings
3. Schedule medium/low priority fixes

## Sign-off
**Security Scan Status:** ✓ PASS | ⚠ WARNINGS | ✗ FAIL

**Approved for merge:** Yes/No
EOF
}
```

### 3. Checkpoint
```bash
if [ "$CRITICAL_ISSUES" -eq 0 ]; then
    checkpoint --phase custom --description "Security scans passed for $TASK_ID" \
        --next "Ready for final review"
else
    checkpoint --phase custom --description "Security scans found $CRITICAL_ISSUES critical issues" \
        --next "Remediate issues before shipping"
fi
```
